Video 13 — Nested Loops

Overview:
Loops inside loops allow working with multi-dimensional structures.

Key Concepts:

Each inner loop completes before the outer loop advances
Useful for grids, matrices, and combinatorics

Example:

for i in range(3):
    for j in range(2):
        print(i, j)

Practical Insights:

Essential for table processing or image/grid tasks
